cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DS

The paper discusses a method and tool for managing scientific hypotheses as uncertain data in a probabilistic database, which involves techniques from database management (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the importance of supporting scientific progress, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE), and the use of immersive and in situ query processing, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
